FBIS3-10313 "drlat044_b_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 Haiti Aristide Spokesman Explains Flynn Visit to Haiti FL0403195494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 GMT 4 Mar 94 FL0403195494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] President Aristide's spokesman Jean-Claude Martineau has pointed out that the visit of the U.S. ambassador to the Vatican was aimed at verifying the distribution of humanitarian aid in Haiti. According to Martineau, shortly before his visit to Haiti, Mr. Flynn had a conversation with President Bill Clinton regarding the restoration of democracy to Haiti within the scope of the Governors Island agreement. For his part, in Paris President Aristide discussed with Mr. Flynn the Vatican's participation in the process of restoring democracy to Haiti. He pointed out that the conversation with the envoy to the Vatican was positive.
